{{Infobox power station | name = Los Barrios | name_official = | image = Central_T%C3%A9rmica_de_Los_Barrios.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Spain | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|36|10|58|N|5|25|12|W|dim:1000_scale:10000_region:ES-TE_type:landmark_source:dewiki|display=it}} | country = Spain | location = [[Los Barrios]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = 1985 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[E.ON]] | operator = [[E.ON]] | th_fuel_primary = [[Coal]] | th_fuel_tertiary = | ps_units_operational = 567&nbsp;MW<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eonespana.com/en/company/generation/coal-fired-power-plants.html | title = E.ON's coal-based thermal power plants | accessdate = 2014-05-29}}</ref> | ps_units_manu_model = General Electric | th_combined_cycle = | ps_electrical_capacity = &nbsp;MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }} The '''Los Barrios Power Plant''' coal-fired [[power station]] is based on the [[Rankine Cycle]]. It is located in the municipality of [[Los Barrios]] in southern Spain, next to the [[Gibraltar-San Roque Refinery]].
The plant is kept in reserve for Spain's electricity grid. It provides direct employment to over 200 employees and it has a capacity of 567.5 MW.
