'''Richland Electric Cooperative''' is an [[Utility cooperative|electric distribution cooperative]] located in [[Richland Center, Wisconsin|Richland Center]], [[Wisconsin]].<ref name="website">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rec.coop/|title=Welcome {{!}} Richland Electric Cooperative|website=www.rec.coop|access-date=2018-08-14}}</ref> Richland Electric Cooperative serves approximately 3500 members with [[Electricity|electric]] service throughout [[Richland County, Wisconsin]] and parts of [[Sauk County, Wisconsin|Sauk]], [[Vernon County, Wisconsin|Vernon]], and [[Crawford County, Wisconsin|Crawford]] counties as well.<ref name=website/>
The cooperative was formed on January 8, 1936 as the '''Richland Cooperative Electric Association''' as the result of the [[Rural Electrification Administration]] order issued by President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] in 1935. It was the first electricity cooperative in the state. The co-op first provided electricity was on May 7, 1937. The farmhouse had been wired for electricity when it was built in the 1917, but had no power grid with which to connect.<ref>"[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=SF0aAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ayoEAAAAIBAJ&pg=4901,9923017 Big switch: Electrification of farms was a welcome and startling development]" ''[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]]'' July 31, 1935, [[Green Sheet (Milwaukee Journal)|Green Sheet]] 1</ref><ref>Wisconsin Rural Electric Cooperative Association, "[http://images.library.wisc.edu/WI/EFacs/USAIN/FirstYear1938/reference/wi.firstyear1938.curti01.pdf Report of Board of Directors of the Wisconsin Rural Electric Cooperative Association]" April 30, 1936.</ref><ref>Perry Baird, "[http://www.wecnmagazine.com/2007issues/may/may07.html Who's On First] {{webarchive|url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20070913051956/http%3A//www.wecnmagazine.com/2007issues/may/may07.html |date=2007-09-13 }}" ''Wisconsin Energy Cooperative News'' May 2007.</ref><ref>"[http://www.wisconsinhistory.org/dictionary/index.asp?action=view&term_id=14827 Rural Electrification (Historic Marker Erected 1965)]" ''Dictionary of Wisconsin History''</ref>
