{{use British English|date=June 2017}} {{use DMY dates|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox lake | name = Ryburn Reservoir | image = File:Ryburn reservoir (1968189176).jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Yorkshire]] | coords = {{coord|53.6652|-1.9693|region:GB|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = United Kingdom | length = | width = | area = {{convert|11|ha|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = {{convert|29|m|abbr=on}} | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | frozen = | islands = | sections = | cities = }} '''Ryburn Reservoir''' is a supply [[reservoir]] operated by [[Yorkshire Water]] close to [[Ripponden]] in the [[Yorkshire]] [[Pennines]], England.<ref>{{cite map|title =South Pennines |map =OL 21 |date = 2015 |scale =1:50,000|series =Explorer |publisher =Ordnance Survey |isbn =9780319242605 }}</ref> It lies in the valley of the [[River Ryburn]] and is the lower of two reservoirs built in the valley to supply [[Wakefield]] with water and was completed in 1933.<ref>[http://www.yorkshirewater.com/recreation/?OBH=53&SCH=ryburn%20reservoir&ID=1487 Ryburn Reservoir, Yorkshire Water]</ref> The upper reservoir is [[Baitings Reservoir]].<ref name=":WTT:">{{cite web|last1=Jacklin|first1=Tim|title=Ryburn Reservoir, West Yorkshire|url=http://www.wildtrout.org/av/ryburn-reservoir-west-yorkshire|website=wildtrout.org|accessdate=19 June 2017|page=3|format=PDF|date=February 2010}}</ref>
Ryburn reservoir is the earlier of the two reservoirs.<ref name=":WTT:" /> It lies just south of the [[A58 road]] and its concrete dam is situated in a deep part of the valley.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Buglas|first1=John|last2=Smith|first2=Linda|title=Ryburn Reservoir, Rishworth, Calderdale|url=http://www.celebrate-our-woodland.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ryburn-final-SEPT2015-.pdf|website=celebrate-our-woodland.co.uk|accessdate=19 June 2017|page=3|format=PDF|date=August 2015}}</ref> Being surrounded by woods, it is a popular area for walkers just outside the settlements of Ripponden and Rishworth.<ref>[http://www.go4awalk.com/ask/ryburn.php Ryburn Reservoir, go4awalk.com]</ref>
